results.name: Smallest number greater than n with exactly the same digits as n in decimal representation, a(n)=10*n if no such number exists.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
program: fromMaybe (10*n) $ find (== a004186 n) $ map a004186 [n+1..10*n]
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Aug 19 2011
